Havel's wife breaks arm, leg in fall on stairs 
Czech President Vaclav Havel's wife, Olga Havlova, is suffering from
arm and leg fractures after slipping and falling on the stairs of the
official residence, the presidential spokesman said Friday.
The head of state's 60-year-old wife fell late Thursday in the Prague
chateau overlooking the city and was hospitalised. She is expected to
need several weeks' rest, he added.
